data.chText: 他的举止完全令人费解。
data.enText: His behaviour was completely beyond comprehension (= impossible to understand) .

data.chText: 她不明白所涉及的事情。
data.enText: She had no comprehension of what was involved.

data.chText: （语言学习中的）理解练习（或训练）
data.enText: an exercise that trains students to understand a language

means: (语言学习中的)理解练习(或训练)

tr: an ability to understand the meaning or importance of something (or the knowledge acquired as a result)
example: how you can do that is beyond my comprehension
he was famous for his comprehension of American literature
he admired the inclusion of so many ideas in such a short work

value.def: Comprehension is the ability to understand something.

example.ex: This was utterly beyond her comprehension.

value.def: Comprehension is full knowledge and understanding of the meaning of something.

example.ex: They turned to one another with the same expression of dawning comprehension, surprise, and relief.
example.tran: 他们相互看了看，脸上都是同一种表情，恍然大悟、惊讶，而又如释重负。

value.def: When pupils do comprehension, they do an exercise to find out how well they understand a piece of spoken or written language.

example.ex: The course also features creative writing exercises and listening comprehension.
example.tran: 这门课程也包括写作练习和听力理解。
